==English==
===Etymology===
From Latin ''[[implicare]]'', "to entangle", "to involve", from ''[[plicare]]'', "to fold", "to twist".
===Verb===
'''to implicate'''
# to show the involvement of someone in something, especially a crime
#:''She implicated several politicians in a bribery scandal.''
